Central European Media Heads for Best Gain in Year on Guidance

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-07-27T13:59:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/central-european-media-heads-for-best-gain-in-year-on-guidance.html
Central European Media Enterprises
Ltd. (CETV)  extended its rally, heading for its biggest gain in more
than a year, after the broadcaster said it expects full-year
revenue of $831 million and operating income before depreciation
and amortization of $168 million today.  CME, as the company is known, jumped 8.4 percent to 334.5
koruna as of 3:45 p.m. in Prague. A close at that level would
mark its biggest one-day advance since May 2010. In U.S.
trading, the stock jumped 11 percent to $20.02 on the Nasdaq
Stock Market.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  